The paper deals with a machine learning problem of supervised clustering, which involves learning a pairwise dissimilarity function. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of hierarchical clustering algorithms, which are commonly used in natural language processing (cs.CL), computer vision (cs.CV), and social network analysis (cs.SI).
